<p>But I do have one tiny request. The comment module has some CSS styling and text formatting surrounding it. For instance it says &#8220;Hi John Smith!&#8221; and &#8220;You are connected with your Facebook account.&#8221;. Each time I update your plugin, I go in and modify that module to use the native CSS styling for my blog and format the text styling too. Is there any way you could turn the styling into text fields in the options page? So that people using it won&#8217;t need to restyle the look each time?</p>
<p>If that&#8217;s a burden or will cause other issues I&#8217;m overlooking, ignore this. <img src="http://ottopress.com/wp-content/plugins/classic-smilies/img/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
